As someone who is already a big proponent of never deviating from basic strategy, this app is a perfect addition to my pre- casino trip practice. What's needed for 5 stars? You miss out on a few key decision moments by not playing the hand out to at least stand or bust. Ex: In >4 deck games, a soft 17 or 18 vs a dealer 6 would lead you to double. However, if you have soft 17 or 18 made up of 3 or more cards (therefore can't double) vs a dealer 6, you should hit with 17 and stand with 18.

I do wish it provided more information about the theory or statistics behind the recommendations, but generally great at what it does.  I like how it breaks down into general training, doubles, and soft trainings so that you can practice your challenge areas

1. I would like to be able to restart my practice from zero.                                           2. I would like an option to get more than just one hit, what I mean is for the game to have a follow through option                         3. Lastly I would like a better explanation when I'm wrong on why I'm wrong

First let me praise the customer support for this product. I wrote Dominik asking for a way to reset the statistics, and a week later the product was updated with that feature!  Other than a few quirks, the user interface is very smooth. An example of what I call a quirk: to get to "Settings" you have to go back to the main menu...the usual (Android-standard) settings button at the bottom of the phone does nothing. Also--and this is NOT a criticism--you should know there is no option to play out the hand. You get to choose a play on the deal; that's all. But this is a trainer, not a game, so I think that is perfectly okay.  I highly recommend this app for learning the basic Blackjack strategy (i.e., without card counting). If the built-in rules for the standard basic strategy don't suit you, you can modify them.
replyContent: Hello Greg, the latest version of BlackJack Trainer Pro allows you to reset statistics! Thanks for your feedback!
